.TH man 1 "13 December 2022" "Holberton shell manual"
.SH NAME
.B hsh
- a simple shell in the style of the shell
.SH SYNPOSIS
.B hsh
.RI [ SCRIPT ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple shell that shares a general syntax with the shell. When run in a terminal, it process commands typed into the terminal. Commands can also be given directly to
.B hsh
on its standard input. Finally,
.B hsh
accepts a single argument,
.I SCRIPT
, that it will execute commands from as if they were passed as input.
.PP
.B hsh
is missing many features from the shell, including quoted and escaped text on the command line, I/O redirection, and command substitution.

